Jeanette Chabalala, News24(Jeanette Chabalala, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein &ndash; A Free State woman watched in despair as a wall fell on her daughter during strong winds&nbsp; on Wednesday afternoon. Another woman was killed in the accident on a&nbsp; horse farm in Douglas Valley, Bloemfontein . &nbsp; "There was a major wind blowing and everyone moved to the wall to avoid the wind, but I decided to hide under the tree," Linda Geldenhuys said."While I was sitting under a tree, I saw the wall falling and I screamed at the top of my lungs for my daughter and the deceased to move away from there, but it was too late," she said. Her daughter Lian&eacute;, 19, survived with serious head injuries.Netcare 911 paramedics said Maurece van Niekerk, 43, died due to extensive injuries she sustained."When I called out to my daughter, she was just lying there and she did not respond, and then my younger daughter called her. She managed to answer. It was a sigh of relief to actually hear her respond, I really thought she was gone," said Geldenhuys.She said she had met Van Niekerk to buy a horse for her younger daughter. The daughter was riding the horse when the accident happened."I really feel so guilty right now that my daughter is alive and I couldn&rsquo;t do anything to help Maurece," said Geldenhuys.Lian&eacute;, a second-year student at the Central University of Technology, was recovering in the Bloemfontein Mediclinic.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.